  "prompt": "What is a sulfuric acid element?",
  "response": "Sulfuric acid (H\u2082SO\u2084) is not an element but a compound composed of the elements sulfur (S), hydrogen (H), and oxygen (O). It is a highly corrosive strong mineral acid that is widely used in various industrial processes, such as fertilizer production, chemical manufacturing, and oil refining.\n\nThe structure of sulfuric acid consists of:\n- Two hydrogen atoms (H),\n- One sulfur atom (S), and\n- Four oxygen atoms (O).\n\nIt is often referred to as a \"chemical workhorse\" due to its versatility and importance in industry.",
